metadata.title: Larvae of Arctic shanny from the Sea of Okhotsk and Bering Sea

creators.name: Oceanogr., Pac. Ocean Sci. Res., Kamchatka Div., Lab. Pelagic Fish

metadata.description:
The article describes larvae of arctic shanny Stichaeus punctatus from 9.9 to
     22.4 mm long, which were caught in waters of the Sea of Okhotsk and
     Bering Sea near Kamchatka. Traits of the larvae are: number of myomeres
     about 55, anteanal distance approximately 40% of body length, small pectoral
     fin, and slanted pigment lines on the sides in the postanal part of the body.
